        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I just started a human necro (level 10 now) that I plan to take to 60, and have some newbie questions :P</P><P>1. I put 25 points into INT, 5 points into STA. Is this a pretty good way to go, or should I have put more into STA? INT seemed logical when I made him, but afterwards I started thinking it'd be way easier max'ing my INT then my STA. My necro is only 10 so I wouldn't mind recreating if this was a bad choice.</P><P>2. One of my two mains is a rogue. Rogues get huge jumps in power at level 10 (backstab, and partial removal of weapon dmg cap), level 55 (double backstab), and level 60 (120 minimum backstab). What are the "big" levels for Necros where there is a major jump in power?</P><P>3. I know of 3 necro spells (funeral pyre, demi-lich, and group DMF) that are very rare & expensive. Since I like to keep an eye open for good deals regardless of what level I am for rare spells, which other ones besides these 3 should I occasionally check for?</P><P>4. Do our pets work with the same level requirements as players to proc weapons? Or can I give my level 8 pet stun whips, DD proc'ing weapons etc?</P><P>5. Human necros have two deity choices (Bertoxx and Inny), I chose Bertoxx. Are there any significant deity-restricted items for necros that make one choice better than the other?</P><P>6. Alteration or Conjuration.. which to specialize in?</P><P>thanks in advance.<BR></font></td>

