        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Then welcome to the wonderfull world of necromancy <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>Firstly, I didnt bother with STA. I took all my points to INT, to gain more mana. We are masters in draining the life from others, so I favored mana over more hp's.</P><P>Secondly, for me I would say lvl16(Feign Death makes the difference),<BR>lvl20 for the first HP to mana conversion and lvl24 for Screaming Terror. Being a lowly lvl30 I will not guess as to how the future levels may be. <img src=icon_smile_wink.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>Third, the pet summoning spells for 20, 24 and 29 can be hard to find. I still use my lvl16 pet, because I havent been able to find / research these. Other than these, spells which are vendor sold at areas in which you are KoS are nice to have an eye out for, for instance in the Bazaar.</P><P>Fourth, in my experience pets do have the same level requirement. But then again I havent researched that very much.</P><P>Fifth, deity wise I would advise you to go with what you want. You could examine, if any quests you want to perform are restricted to any deity, especially your epic which may be Innoruuk only. I dont know if the epic is restricted that way, but its the only thing i would imagine that could influence your choice.</P><P>Sixth, Alteration are the way to go IMHO. Our DoTs are mostly Alt-based.</P><P>Have fun with your necro <img src=icon_smile_big.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>Xhiran Jadeclaw, 30th Follower of Cazic-Thule<BR>Antonius Bayle</P><P>_____________________________________<BR>A man asked Hakuin, a Zen master, "What happens after we die?"<BR>The master replied, "I don't know."<BR>"What do you mean? You're a Zen master, aren't you?"<BR>"I am," came the reply, "but not a dead one."</P><P>Zen koan<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
