         1) My necro was my first main.  I put most of my points into int and then a few into str I think =(  I think STA is a much better choice.  You are correct that getting high Int will be fairly easy but you will also be able to find a lot of +hp items (you have a 60 rogue so pp shouldn't be a problem).  I wouldn't reroll.</P><P>2) Hmmm.  Well the absolute level for a necro is 49.  You get Lich, Bond of Death and the 49 pet.  Very big moment.  VI may have added spells to the lower levels that are similar to lich and bond of death, so maybe it isn't as big a deal now as it was then.  At level 24 you get a nice DD that can even out DD wizards (again, at least when I was 24 2.5 years ago).  Getting summon corpse at 39 is nice.</P><P>3) Our 59 pet can be quite rare and hard to get as well.  Emissory of Thule.  I see them in bazaar from 10 to 16k.  Some servers much higher.</P><P>6) Definitely Alt.</P><P>Good luck and have fun.</P><P>Edit: At level 24 your pet gets double attack and at 29 he gets dual wield.  Those are big moments as well as you start to see your pet take over the fights as your best DoT.</P><P></P><P><BR>Edited by - Tvenya on 10/08/2002  09:12:22<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
