        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         1. STA won't net you too many hp at the upper end that won't be taken care of by gear. No worries. </P><P>2. Power jumps: 16 (Feign Death). Practice this often, success is tied in to your Abjuration skill. Also, 29, when you go from being able to stack about 300 hp worth of DoTs to stacking over 1k. Plus, your pet dual wields here, and finally surpasses you in your ability to tank. Before then you do its job for it. ;) 49 is a necro dream level, from what I gather.</P><P>3. I'm not sure, but someone once told me to look out for Quivering Veil of Xarn as they'd had trouble finding it themselves. </P><P>4. Yes, they do. However, be aware that your level does not equal the pet's level. While we say "our 29 pet", the 29 pet is actually a level 26 mob...and so on. Thus, be aware of what level your pet is before giving him a proc'ing weapon he won't be able to use. This is only based on my own experience with Velium Weapons.</P><P>5. Inny is better, simply because it is very difficult to find worshippers of Bertoxx that are able to imbue gems for deity-specific goodies. I know our local server board always has people trying to find anyone who plays a Bertox worshipping cleric..</P><P>6. Alteration or Conjuration? I'm not qualified to answer..I went with Alteration based on instinct. I could easily be wrong. :)</P><P></P><P><img src="http://www.greendragoons.com/hrensig.gif" border=0><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85371">Hrendra An'ei</a> • 53 Reaver<BR>Hrett Mai’ru • 39 Mage<BR>Sorchai Ni’Cràdh • 29 Necromancer<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
